1
00:00:02,069 --> 00:00:03,738
Completely unfazed by the crisis mode

2
00:00:03,804 --> 00:00:06,273
of disaster stricken Japan,

3
00:00:06,540 --> 00:00:09,143
Tokyo is filled with excitement
for the Olympics

4
00:00:09,210 --> 00:00:10,678
being held in the city next year.

5
00:00:11,412 --> 00:00:15,783
But there is a mysterious woman
who quietly runs Sanchi Real Estate

6
00:00:16,417 --> 00:00:19,220
in this community full of vacant houses,

7
00:00:19,687 --> 00:00:21,322
away from the busy city.

8
00:00:21,889 --> 00:00:25,126
This is the woman who was feared,
respected, and revered

9
00:00:25,626 --> 00:00:26,827
by everyone

10
00:00:26,894 --> 00:00:28,362
in the real estate industry.

11
00:00:28,763 --> 00:00:31,766
She's the genius realtor, Machi Sangenya.

12
00:00:32,366 --> 00:00:33,868
The living legend.

13
00:00:34,168 --> 00:00:35,903
Go! Go! Go!

14
00:00:37,872 --> 00:00:39,306
SANCHI REAL ESTATE

15
00:00:50,951 --> 00:00:52,119
-Manager.
-Oh!

16
00:00:53,687 --> 00:00:56,257
Welcome back. It must have been cold out.

17
00:00:56,957 --> 00:00:58,826
The last property was sold.

18
00:00:58,893 --> 00:01:01,996
Oh, good work.

19
00:01:02,062 --> 00:01:04,265
Then our job here is done.

20
00:01:04,331 --> 00:01:08,702
Yes, all the vacant properties
in this town have been sold.

21
00:01:08,769 --> 00:01:11,505
It wasn't you. I sold them all.

22
00:01:11,972 --> 00:01:15,142
It wasn't me, the manager,
but you, the president, who sold it.

23
00:01:15,509 --> 00:01:17,077
I'll help you pack.

24
00:01:17,144 --> 00:01:19,580
No, the packing is all done.

25
00:01:20,080 --> 00:01:25,753
What's left is to pack our futon
tomorrow, and then we can "Go!"

26
00:01:26,921 --> 00:01:29,723
In that case, Manager, let's get it on.

27
00:01:30,691 --> 00:01:32,493
What? Get it on?

28
00:01:33,027 --> 00:01:35,729
It's our last night in this town.

29
00:01:36,163 --> 00:01:37,264
TAMPOPO MOVING COMPANY

30
00:01:37,331 --> 00:01:39,567
Well, um…

31
00:01:40,234 --> 00:01:43,571
It's not quite night time yet.
It's still bright out.

32
00:01:43,637 --> 00:01:46,173
If we close the shutters,
it's just like night time.

33
00:01:46,474 --> 00:01:48,142
Go to bed now!

34
00:01:48,209 --> 00:01:49,477
Yes!

35
00:02:03,891 --> 00:02:06,193
Cheers!

36
00:02:09,096 --> 00:02:12,533
Ready? Thank you for all your great work.

37
00:02:12,600 --> 00:02:14,034
Good job.

38
00:02:14,101 --> 00:02:15,803
Thank you. Thank you.

39
00:02:15,870 --> 00:02:18,606
After I became the Manager
the sales went down,

40
00:02:18,672 --> 00:02:20,574
but I'm glad I was able to welcome

41
00:02:20,641 --> 00:02:22,910
my final day as the Manager
without too much trouble.

42
00:02:22,977 --> 00:02:24,278
I'm happy.

43
00:02:24,345 --> 00:02:27,214
Starting next week,
I'll be a long-awaited contract worker!

44
00:02:27,281 --> 00:02:28,582
Yeah!

45
00:02:28,649 --> 00:02:31,418
Oh, Teiko Real Estate Company
brings back memories.

46
00:02:31,819 --> 00:02:35,656
That's where I spent my youth,
filled with memories of love and hatred.

47
00:02:35,723 --> 00:02:38,492
Shirasu, you quit
without selling any properties.

48
00:02:38,559 --> 00:02:40,327
Mr. Adachi!

49
00:02:40,394 --> 00:02:43,264
You're cute and are my type,

50
00:02:43,330 --> 00:02:46,600
but your comment just now
was a bit too mean.

51
00:02:46,667 --> 00:02:49,236
It's true that you didn't sell
a single property!

52
00:02:49,703 --> 00:02:51,572
Why are you working here anyway,
Ms. Shirasu?

53
00:02:52,039 --> 00:02:56,677
If I don't have a job,
I can't put my kids in preschool.

54
00:02:56,744 --> 00:02:59,780
I'm a poor single mother.

55
00:02:59,847 --> 00:03:03,484
Takuma was telling me.
You have your mom raising your kids.

56
00:03:03,551 --> 00:03:05,219
No need for you
to send them to a preschool.

57
00:03:05,286 --> 00:03:07,121
But I have two kids.

58
00:03:07,187 --> 00:03:09,189
My mother will die from being overworked.

59
00:03:09,623 --> 00:03:12,026
You just need to raise
your own kids properly.

60
00:03:12,092 --> 00:03:14,995
He's right. There was no need
for you to divorce Mr. Takuma either.

61
00:03:15,062 --> 00:03:17,331
Right. You two were a perfect couple,
about the same caliber.

62
00:03:20,534 --> 00:03:22,536
What is this? You're all picking on me!

63
00:03:22,603 --> 00:03:26,273
There, there. This is her trial period,
so just bear with us.

64
00:03:26,340 --> 00:03:29,209
Mika said it's fine to fire her
if she's no good.

65
00:03:29,276 --> 00:03:32,046
If I get fired, I might go back
to Teiko Real Estate.

66
00:03:33,347 --> 00:03:36,317
-Did you just say "yuck"?
-No, calm down.

67
00:03:36,383 --> 00:03:39,753
If I was still the manager,
that could've been an option.

68
00:03:39,820 --> 00:03:43,390
But starting next Monday,
per the headquarters' ardent request,

69
00:03:43,757 --> 00:03:47,695
Manager Yashiro and Sanchi
are coming back to sales.

70
00:03:47,761 --> 00:03:49,263
That's right.

71
00:03:49,330 --> 00:03:50,664
I like Manager Yashiro,

72
00:03:50,731 --> 00:03:53,500
but if that woman is coming back, no way!

73
00:03:53,567 --> 00:03:56,770
Even if they beg me to come back,
I won't work at Teiko Real Estate.

74
00:03:56,837 --> 00:04:01,208
I will never forgive that monstrous woman

75
00:04:01,275 --> 00:04:02,910
who fired me!

76
00:04:02,977 --> 00:04:05,713
No good will come from
hating someone so much.

77
00:04:06,580 --> 00:04:10,818
Chief Sangenya got married
to Manager Yashiro,

78
00:04:12,786 --> 00:04:14,521
so should we call her Chief Yashiro?

79
00:04:14,989 --> 00:04:16,624
I should be the only chief.

80
00:04:16,690 --> 00:04:20,828
No, it's fine calling them
Manager Yashiro and Chief Sangenya.

81
00:04:21,261 --> 00:04:24,531
In this real estate industry,
everyone knows Machi Sangenya,

82
00:04:24,999 --> 00:04:27,968
but Machi Yashiro?
Everyone will be like, "Who is that?"

83
00:04:28,435 --> 00:04:29,637
Right.

84
00:04:29,703 --> 00:04:33,040
She will always be Chief Sangenya to us.
I can't wait to see her.

85
00:04:33,107 --> 00:04:34,975
You were Sanchi's dog, after all.

86
00:04:35,242 --> 00:04:37,778
I'm not her dog.
I'm one of the "Sangenya Children".

87
00:04:38,212 --> 00:04:39,713
You are a dog! You are Sanchi's dog.

88
00:04:39,780 --> 00:04:41,582
-I am not her dog.
-Mika!

89
00:04:41,649 --> 00:04:43,584
TEIKO REAL ESTATE

90
00:04:45,119 --> 00:04:46,120
How does it look?

91
00:04:46,186 --> 00:04:47,554
Huh? I think it's good.

92
00:04:48,555 --> 00:04:51,191
-What is that?
-I don't know.

93
00:04:51,258 --> 00:04:55,562
Good morning! I'm Makoto Fuse,
a first year contract worker!

94
00:04:56,130 --> 00:04:57,431
What are you doing?

95
00:04:57,498 --> 00:05:00,234
It's a party ball to welcome back
Manager Yashiro and Chief Sangenya.

96
00:05:00,634 --> 00:05:03,771
You are definitely a Sangenya Children.
A party ball, huh?

97
00:05:03,837 --> 00:05:05,839
-Very devoted.
-Very devoted for sure.

98
00:05:05,906 --> 00:05:08,709
Everyone,
once I put my hand on the string,

99
00:05:08,776 --> 00:05:10,678
clap and liven up the atmosphere, okay?

100
00:05:11,178 --> 00:05:13,514
I think your dear Chief Sangenya
is about to arrive soon.

101
00:05:14,081 --> 00:05:15,683
Mr. Takuma is waiting by the elevator.

102
00:05:15,983 --> 00:05:17,251
Oh, is that why he was there?

103
00:05:17,317 --> 00:05:19,086
Hey, hey!

104
00:05:19,153 --> 00:05:21,155
The elevator is coming up right now!

105
00:05:21,221 --> 00:05:24,558
I suspect Manager
and Chief Sangenya are on it!

106
00:05:25,159 --> 00:05:27,394
-Everyone, get in position!
-Get ready.

107
00:05:33,000 --> 00:05:35,002
Morning, everyone!

108
00:05:35,436 --> 00:05:37,671
Good morning.

109
00:05:37,738 --> 00:05:38,739
I'm back!

110
00:05:38,806 --> 00:05:40,841
We've been waiting for you,
Manager Yashiro!

111
00:05:40,908 --> 00:05:42,843
Mr. Fuse, it's been a while!

112
00:05:42,910 --> 00:05:44,712
Creepy.

113
00:05:45,546 --> 00:05:46,747
Um…

114
00:05:48,148 --> 00:05:49,316
Where's Chief Sangenya?

115
00:05:49,616 --> 00:05:52,920
Oh, once Sangenya knew
we were coming back,

116
00:05:52,986 --> 00:05:55,589
she made several appointments
and went to make sales calls already.

117
00:05:55,656 --> 00:05:57,291
Wow, she sure is good.

118
00:06:00,227 --> 00:06:01,862
What is this?

119
00:06:01,929 --> 00:06:03,464
It's a party ball to welcome you two back.

120
00:06:03,731 --> 00:06:06,033
Wow! Could you open it? Open it!

121
00:06:06,100 --> 00:06:07,568
Once Chief Sangenya gets back.

122
00:06:08,602 --> 00:06:11,972
Chief Sangenya will close the deal
by lunch, so we will then open it.

123
00:06:12,039 --> 00:06:15,242
Niwano!
Do not underestimate real estate sales!

124
00:06:15,309 --> 00:06:17,444
It's not that easy even
for that Sangenya--

125
00:06:17,511 --> 00:06:18,512
Manager!

126
00:06:19,179 --> 00:06:21,415
I've sold the 33 square-meter house
in Musashino.

127
00:06:22,116 --> 00:06:25,552
I sold it for ¥28 million
to a confined property enthusiast.

128
00:06:26,587 --> 00:06:28,021
Way to go, Sangenya!

129
00:06:28,088 --> 00:06:29,323
Congrats.

130
00:06:29,389 --> 00:06:30,591
-Niwano!
-Oh, yes!

131
00:06:30,958 --> 00:06:32,559
-Ouch!
-Hey!

132
00:06:32,626 --> 00:06:34,261
-How lame.
-Niwano!

133
00:06:34,528 --> 00:06:35,996
-Manager!
-Yes!

134
00:06:36,530 --> 00:06:37,798
It's time for the morning meeting.

135
00:06:37,865 --> 00:06:42,136
Right. Everyone is here now,
so let's have a morning meeting.

136
00:06:42,603 --> 00:06:45,439
Well, a lot has happened.

137
00:06:45,939 --> 00:06:48,742
But being able to come back here

138
00:06:48,809 --> 00:06:52,112
to the Teiko Real Estate Shinjuku Office
Real Estate Brokerage Division

139
00:06:52,746 --> 00:06:53,981
is making me so emotional.

140
00:06:55,949 --> 00:06:58,418
Let's all work together

141
00:06:58,485 --> 00:07:03,223
to benefit the customers
as well as the company.

142
00:07:03,690 --> 00:07:05,058
Yes.

143
00:07:05,125 --> 00:07:06,193
Manager Yashiro.

144
00:07:06,827 --> 00:07:08,228
This is Kagimura who started last year,

145
00:07:08,529 --> 00:07:10,998
and this is Tokoshima
who started this year.

146
00:07:11,064 --> 00:07:15,202
Tokoshima, the copy machine
is out of A4 paper. Refill it right now.

147
00:07:15,269 --> 00:07:17,104
I'll take care of it later.

148
00:07:17,171 --> 00:07:19,740
Please don't address me like that.

149
00:07:20,040 --> 00:07:21,642
Tokoshima, do it now.

150
00:07:21,708 --> 00:07:22,709
Go!

151
00:07:25,412 --> 00:07:27,481
Even Tokoshima can't win
against that "Go!"

152
00:07:27,548 --> 00:07:29,650
Niwano, what's your schedule today?

153
00:07:29,950 --> 00:07:32,119
-I have an appointment in the morning.
-Then?

154
00:07:32,186 --> 00:07:33,220
There's nothing after that.

155
00:07:33,287 --> 00:07:34,288
Chief Adachi?

156
00:07:34,788 --> 00:07:36,223
As a chief I am more--

157
00:07:36,290 --> 00:07:38,058
That's not necessary.
What is your schedule today?

158
00:07:38,992 --> 00:07:42,329
I have two viewings, one contract,
and a meeting with a seller.

159
00:07:42,763 --> 00:07:44,598
-Why do I need to tell you--
-Mr. Hachinohe?

160
00:07:44,932 --> 00:07:47,534
-I'll go meet a Chinese investor now.
-Mr. Takuma?

161
00:07:47,601 --> 00:07:48,969
I don't have any plans. I apologize.

162
00:07:49,036 --> 00:07:51,271
Fuse will go over things with the Manager.

163
00:07:51,338 --> 00:07:53,440
-Kagimura?
-I don't have any plans.

164
00:07:54,208 --> 00:07:56,109
Kagimura, what are your sales
for this month?

165
00:07:56,844 --> 00:07:58,779
-It's zero.
-Last month's sales?

166
00:07:59,112 --> 00:08:00,714
-It's zero.
-The month before that?

167
00:08:00,781 --> 00:08:02,850
-It's zero.
-Sales before that month?

168
00:08:02,916 --> 00:08:05,352
Now, now, Sangenya.
It's our first day back…

169
00:08:05,419 --> 00:08:08,188
Kagimura, start cold calling
the customers on the contact list.

170
00:08:08,589 --> 00:08:10,090
No, I'm handing out flyers as Sumo-kun.

171
00:08:10,157 --> 00:08:13,126
I told you to make some calls. Call!

172
00:08:13,193 --> 00:08:14,194
Go!

173
00:08:14,895 --> 00:08:16,630
Hello? Hello?

174
00:08:16,697 --> 00:08:18,498
Mr. Takuma, post the flyers.

175
00:08:18,565 --> 00:08:19,600
-Go!
-Yes!

176
00:08:19,666 --> 00:08:21,735
Do you have any other requests?

177
00:08:22,336 --> 00:08:26,173
It feels like it's a brand new company.

178
00:08:28,275 --> 00:08:32,112
Let's see. It's Shinjuku district,
Shinjuku west…

179
00:08:32,880 --> 00:08:36,183
Nine, nine…

180
00:08:36,250 --> 00:08:37,985
Two, three.

181
00:08:38,051 --> 00:08:39,686
Two, three. What?

182
00:08:40,554 --> 00:08:43,357
-I will come along.
-Yes!

183
00:08:47,694 --> 00:08:51,999
Today's client is a couple in their 50s
looking for a home after retirement.

184
00:08:52,065 --> 00:08:53,200
What are their names?

185
00:08:53,700 --> 00:08:56,136
-It's Mr. and Mrs. Hanada.
-What are their first names?

186
00:08:56,837 --> 00:08:59,773
It's Mr. Haruo Hanada, and um--

187
00:08:59,840 --> 00:09:01,441
It's Mrs. Eriko Hanada.

188
00:09:02,075 --> 00:09:03,777
Oh, you knew.

189
00:09:04,311 --> 00:09:07,681
Someone who doesn't know the customer's
full name can't sell a house.

190
00:09:08,582 --> 00:09:10,684
And the party ball didn't open either.

191
00:09:11,218 --> 00:09:14,855
I will sell a property to Mr. Haruo Hanada
and Mrs. Eriko Hanada.

192
00:09:14,922 --> 00:09:16,189
What?

193
00:09:16,256 --> 00:09:19,026
There is no property I can't sell!

194
00:09:36,944 --> 00:09:38,045
Here you go.

195
00:09:40,147 --> 00:09:42,849
No one will take it.

196
00:09:43,850 --> 00:09:46,219
-Can I get one?
-Please.

197
00:09:56,263 --> 00:09:58,465
I'm cold! A real mental breakdown.

198
00:09:58,532 --> 00:10:02,002
Kagimura, you just went out there
a minute ago!

199
00:10:02,069 --> 00:10:03,603
But Manager,

200
00:10:03,670 --> 00:10:07,207
Sumo-kun is cold
in the winter and hot in the summer.

201
00:10:07,674 --> 00:10:09,843
-What?
-There, there.

202
00:10:10,444 --> 00:10:11,745
It's this day and age.

203
00:10:12,012 --> 00:10:14,781
My Sumo-kun is not getting
any subscribers.

204
00:10:17,884 --> 00:10:19,419
Kagi Channel!

205
00:10:19,953 --> 00:10:23,223
Sumo-kun is Teiko Real Estate's mascot.

206
00:10:23,290 --> 00:10:25,792
If you are interested, please,

207
00:10:26,193 --> 00:10:27,661
subscribe to this channel!

208
00:10:27,728 --> 00:10:29,997
How boring is that!

209
00:10:30,063 --> 00:10:31,064
What?

210
00:10:31,131 --> 00:10:33,066
If you're gonna post on YouTube, do this.

211
00:10:33,133 --> 00:10:36,236
Nikumaru Nikumaru, Jirushi!

212
00:10:36,303 --> 00:10:37,938
Nikumaru Jirushi!

213
00:10:38,572 --> 00:10:40,374
I will be using this today!

214
00:10:40,841 --> 00:10:43,443
The content inside is iced coffee.

215
00:10:43,510 --> 00:10:49,549
I'll see how people will react
when I drink this in public!

216
00:10:49,616 --> 00:10:54,121
-Nikumaru!
-Oh boy…

217
00:10:56,189 --> 00:10:57,190
Do you want to die?

218
00:10:57,257 --> 00:11:00,093
You must be going through
something difficult huh!?

219
00:11:00,160 --> 00:11:01,361
Nikumaru.

220
00:11:01,428 --> 00:11:04,531
Old Man, this is actually iced coffee!

221
00:11:05,499 --> 00:11:06,433
Nikumaru!

222
00:11:06,867 --> 00:11:09,436
You dare to make fun of old people?

223
00:11:09,503 --> 00:11:12,773
The prank was a success!

224
00:11:12,839 --> 00:11:13,840
Subscribe to my channel!

225
00:11:13,907 --> 00:11:15,909
What is this?

226
00:11:15,976 --> 00:11:17,144
It's Nikumaru's videos.

227
00:11:17,511 --> 00:11:19,246
Nikumaru? What is Nikumaru?

228
00:11:19,679 --> 00:11:21,214
He's a YouTuber!

229
00:11:21,281 --> 00:11:24,418
Nikumaru, Nikumaru, Jirushi.

230
00:11:24,484 --> 00:11:26,119
Nikumaru Jirushi!

231
00:11:28,121 --> 00:11:31,625
Today, I'm going to take

232
00:11:31,691 --> 00:11:34,995
a very fancy bath!

233
00:11:35,062 --> 00:11:36,329
Nikumaru.

234
00:11:37,831 --> 00:11:39,933
Wow!

235
00:11:42,803 --> 00:11:43,737
Nikumaru.

236
00:11:44,004 --> 00:11:46,940
It's a bath with Nishikigoi carp!

237
00:11:47,374 --> 00:11:51,711
The total is… yen!

238
00:11:51,778 --> 00:11:55,282
Please subscribe to the channel!

239
00:11:56,149 --> 00:11:57,484
ANTI-NIKUMARU
DON'T GET CARRIED AWAY!

240
00:11:57,551 --> 00:11:59,186
How stupid is that?

241
00:11:59,519 --> 00:12:00,587
What's so funny about it?

242
00:12:00,654 --> 00:12:05,225
YouTubing is the most desirable job
a kid wants to have.

243
00:12:05,292 --> 00:12:06,827
It's the end of the world!

244
00:12:06,893 --> 00:12:10,197
A desirable job? This is a job?

245
00:12:10,263 --> 00:12:12,632
You don't get it, do you?

246
00:12:13,166 --> 00:12:17,170
A popular YouTuber
can make over ¥100 million.

247
00:12:18,605 --> 00:12:19,673
What? ¥100 million?

248
00:12:19,940 --> 00:12:21,475
It's not just ¥100 million.

249
00:12:21,541 --> 00:12:23,276
It's several hundred million a year!

250
00:12:23,343 --> 00:12:25,345
Several hundred million?

251
00:12:25,412 --> 00:12:28,315
Even so, what if the kids copied him?

252
00:12:28,882 --> 00:12:31,985
That's not the issue.

253
00:12:32,052 --> 00:12:34,020
-Go for it.
-What is it then?

254
00:12:34,354 --> 00:12:36,723
If you don't understand this appeal,

255
00:12:36,790 --> 00:12:39,292
I don't think you can sell houses
to the younger generation.

256
00:12:39,726 --> 00:12:42,762
Wow, is that so, Tokoshima?

257
00:12:42,829 --> 00:12:45,599
So what? Kagimura watches that

258
00:12:45,665 --> 00:12:49,169
-but has he sold a single house?
-Toko!

259
00:12:49,236 --> 00:12:50,804
Don't make things complicated!

260
00:12:50,871 --> 00:12:54,274
-Alrighty.
-Um…

261
00:12:54,341 --> 00:12:58,912
Television shows
are more orthodox and safer to watch.

262
00:12:58,979 --> 00:13:03,283
The shows that air on TV
go through several quality controls,

263
00:13:03,350 --> 00:13:08,288
so it's proper and totally different
from unregulated uploads.

264
00:13:08,722 --> 00:13:11,791
It's interesting
because it is an unregulated upload.

265
00:13:12,592 --> 00:13:14,294
I don't get what you are saying!

266
00:13:14,361 --> 00:13:16,963
Yes, I don't get it.
I'm going to the restroom.

267
00:13:18,398 --> 00:13:21,601
It is smaller
compared to where you reside now,

268
00:13:22,035 --> 00:13:26,740
but its layout and facilities
are perfect for a couple like yourselves.

269
00:13:27,307 --> 00:13:29,009
Each floor has a trash area--

270
00:13:29,075 --> 00:13:31,511
I don't want to live so high up.

271
00:13:31,578 --> 00:13:33,446
The view is great.

272
00:13:33,513 --> 00:13:36,416
The view? You'll be tired of it in a week!

273
00:13:36,850 --> 00:13:38,051
You think so?

274
00:13:39,819 --> 00:13:41,855
Then I'll look for another property.

275
00:13:41,922 --> 00:13:43,990
I'm sort of tired now.

276
00:13:45,225 --> 00:13:46,226
Nino?

277
00:13:46,560 --> 00:13:47,694
I'm Niwano.

278
00:13:48,061 --> 00:13:49,763
Can you take me home?

279
00:13:51,731 --> 00:13:54,067
Thank you for stopping
by the grocery store for me.

280
00:13:54,868 --> 00:13:56,469
We will be leaving now.

281
00:13:56,536 --> 00:14:00,407
Wait. Can you place
all the stuff I bought in the fridge?

282
00:14:00,974 --> 00:14:02,976
-What?
-We will come in.

283
00:14:21,428 --> 00:14:22,696
Nino!

284
00:14:23,029 --> 00:14:24,064
My name is Niwano.

285
00:14:24,130 --> 00:14:28,034
I'm sorry. Niwano,
could you please fold these?

286
00:14:28,368 --> 00:14:31,071
I hate folding laundry the most!

287
00:14:32,105 --> 00:14:35,942
Then, I'll open the fridge.

288
00:14:36,209 --> 00:14:37,244
Please.

289
00:14:38,612 --> 00:14:42,415
Go ahead and have any juice
or tea in the fridge.

290
00:14:42,482 --> 00:14:43,650
Thank you very much.

291
00:14:48,121 --> 00:14:49,956
-Okay.
-Are you done?

292
00:14:50,023 --> 00:14:52,459
-Yes.
-Then could you massage my back?

293
00:14:52,525 --> 00:14:53,994
What? Oh? Yes!

294
00:14:56,463 --> 00:14:57,731
-Excuse me.
-Yes.

295
00:14:59,432 --> 00:15:00,500
That feels nice.

296
00:15:04,170 --> 00:15:07,841
-I actually want to get a divorce.
-What?

297
00:15:08,208 --> 00:15:11,344
Everyone is enjoying life
divorcing their husband after retirement.

298
00:15:12,078 --> 00:15:14,180
I don't think it's everyone.

299
00:15:14,247 --> 00:15:18,184
My husband snores like a pig.

300
00:15:18,251 --> 00:15:21,154
When I hear it, I get murderous thoughts
in the middle of the night.

301
00:15:21,554 --> 00:15:26,326
And what am I going to do
if he's home every day after retirement?

302
00:15:27,260 --> 00:15:28,962
Right,

303
00:15:29,029 --> 00:15:30,864
so I think

304
00:15:30,930 --> 00:15:35,201
I'll go crazy if he is home every day.

305
00:15:35,502 --> 00:15:37,971
Even if I die because of that,

306
00:15:38,038 --> 00:15:41,775
I'll be placed
in the same grave as him, right?

307
00:15:42,876 --> 00:15:46,513
I'll be with him
under the same stone forever, right?

308
00:15:47,247 --> 00:15:49,916
I can't handle that! I can't do it!

309
00:15:50,517 --> 00:15:53,019
I feel so bad for myself.

310
00:15:53,553 --> 00:15:57,891
Mr. Haruo Hanada
has no clue about how you feel,

311
00:15:58,425 --> 00:16:02,462
and is searching for a home
to live with you after he retires?

312
00:16:03,163 --> 00:16:04,264
He's stupid, right?

313
00:16:04,331 --> 00:16:06,099
I feel sorry for him a little.

314
00:16:06,166 --> 00:16:09,936
I'm telling you
that you should feel sorry for me.

315
00:16:10,637 --> 00:16:13,206
Um… Ni… wano!

316
00:16:14,007 --> 00:16:17,310
Can you search for a home
I could live in by myself? Rental is fine.

317
00:16:18,178 --> 00:16:19,846
What is your budget?

318
00:16:20,313 --> 00:16:23,483
Let's see,
a ten year lease for ¥1 million.

319
00:16:27,487 --> 00:16:31,424
You are not sorry at all!
This is a press conference to apologize!

320
00:16:31,491 --> 00:16:34,160
Does it matter? Everyone enjoyed it!

321
00:16:34,627 --> 00:16:39,799
It's all because of people like you guys
who talk of regulatory compliances,

322
00:16:39,866 --> 00:16:43,436
that this country became boring as heck!

323
00:16:43,503 --> 00:16:44,971
Don't change the subject!

324
00:16:45,038 --> 00:16:46,573
Apologize properly!

325
00:16:46,639 --> 00:16:48,641
I won't apologize!

326
00:16:48,708 --> 00:16:51,378
I'll continue to upload extreme
and funny videos!

327
00:16:51,444 --> 00:16:52,512
I know!

328
00:16:53,113 --> 00:16:57,584
I'll eat 100 caterpillars next time!

329
00:17:02,789 --> 00:17:05,191
About 100 of them are telling you
to eat caterpillars.

330
00:17:05,592 --> 00:17:07,694
If I don't do it,
I'll come under fire on the net.

331
00:17:08,128 --> 00:17:09,829
It's the same even if I do it.

332
00:17:09,896 --> 00:17:11,765
It's because you opened your big mouth.

333
00:17:12,699 --> 00:17:14,601
How many more videos do I have in stock?

334
00:17:15,902 --> 00:17:18,104
Takoyaki snow ball fight that
you recently shot,

335
00:17:18,171 --> 00:17:20,440
and Kagami dumpling versus a hard skull.

336
00:17:20,507 --> 00:17:21,608
That's it?

337
00:17:23,076 --> 00:17:28,581
What? I'll really have to eat
caterpillars then…

338
00:17:29,249 --> 00:17:33,119
It's the norm for a popular YouTuber
to upload daily.

339
00:17:33,853 --> 00:17:36,823
You are losing subscribers,
so this is the time to pick things up.

340
00:17:38,591 --> 00:17:40,059
Now, good work.

341
00:17:40,126 --> 00:17:42,862
What? Could you stay a little longer?

342
00:17:42,929 --> 00:17:44,664
Ever since my address was revealed
on the net,

343
00:17:44,731 --> 00:17:45,932
someone is always out there.

344
00:17:45,999 --> 00:17:49,002
I can't. I have a meeting with another
YouTuber now.

345
00:18:16,930 --> 00:18:17,997
Here you go.

346
00:18:18,798 --> 00:18:19,966
Here you go.

347
00:18:21,968 --> 00:18:23,603
Oh?

348
00:18:24,170 --> 00:18:27,240
There's a Sumo wrestler
with a strange face!

349
00:18:27,307 --> 00:18:28,842
Wow! It's Nikumaru!

350
00:18:29,542 --> 00:18:32,745
Please subscribe to my channel!

351
00:18:33,046 --> 00:18:34,247
Well… Right?

352
00:18:36,382 --> 00:18:37,917
We have a client!

353
00:18:37,984 --> 00:18:41,187
This is the brokerage section.

354
00:18:41,254 --> 00:18:43,323
This graph is their sales records.

355
00:18:43,590 --> 00:18:46,459
The one selling the most is Adachi!

356
00:18:47,060 --> 00:18:49,929
-I think I've seen him somewhere before.
-What?

357
00:18:50,630 --> 00:18:52,465
That's the one drinking
the fake soy sauce!

358
00:18:56,503 --> 00:18:58,238
I only watch TV,

359
00:18:58,304 --> 00:19:02,375
so excuse me
for not knowing you were very famous.

360
00:19:02,442 --> 00:19:05,945
That's fine,
but what do you like about TV?

361
00:19:06,846 --> 00:19:07,981
What do you mean?

362
00:19:08,915 --> 00:19:10,416
Oh, forget it.

363
00:19:10,717 --> 00:19:14,721
So I want a house and I have funds.

364
00:19:15,588 --> 00:19:17,056
If it's one or two hundred million,

365
00:19:17,457 --> 00:19:20,159
-I'll buy it with cash!
-Cash?

366
00:19:20,660 --> 00:19:25,131
Find me a house that'll protect me
from the public eye!

367
00:19:26,466 --> 00:19:28,034
As you wish.

368
00:19:28,101 --> 00:19:31,204
I will search for a house
with the latest security!

369
00:19:31,871 --> 00:19:36,009
Well, Nikumaru's time
is about to end soon.

370
00:19:36,943 --> 00:19:39,746
The number of subscribers
has decreased drastically.

371
00:19:40,880 --> 00:19:42,815
It's the rise and fall of life.

372
00:19:43,416 --> 00:19:44,450
What is that?

373
00:19:44,517 --> 00:19:47,520
I have a first level certificate
in four character idioms.

374
00:19:49,355 --> 00:19:51,624
All that prospers must decline.

375
00:19:56,763 --> 00:19:58,031
Touche, pointe.

376
00:19:59,065 --> 00:20:01,000
En garde, prêt, allez.

377
00:20:01,501 --> 00:20:03,202
Mr. Adachi, good evening.

378
00:20:03,269 --> 00:20:04,804
Ah, good evening.

379
00:20:04,871 --> 00:20:07,740
I'll work up a sweat tonight again
before I go home.

380
00:20:09,909 --> 00:20:11,210
Winner, Rusudo.

381
00:20:14,647 --> 00:20:17,050
Oh, good timing. Rusudo!

382
00:20:20,753 --> 00:20:22,021
Good evening.

383
00:20:22,088 --> 00:20:23,856
This is Kenji Rusudo.

384
00:20:24,624 --> 00:20:25,692
This is Mr. Adachi.

385
00:20:26,092 --> 00:20:28,428
I'm Rusudo. Nice to meet you.

386
00:20:28,494 --> 00:20:30,363
I'm Adachi. Nice to meet you.

387
00:20:30,997 --> 00:20:32,999
Could we give it a go?

388
00:20:34,434 --> 00:20:35,501
I'd be glad to.

389
00:20:40,807 --> 00:20:41,941
Touche, pointe.

390
00:20:43,910 --> 00:20:45,645
En garde, prêt, allez.

391
00:20:49,749 --> 00:20:51,084
Winner, Rusudo.

392
00:21:01,461 --> 00:21:02,829
Thank you very much.

393
00:21:05,698 --> 00:21:08,668
This is the first time
someone beat you, Mr. Adachi.

394
00:21:16,476 --> 00:21:18,011
Don't pull it, push it.

395
00:21:19,712 --> 00:21:20,780
Push?

396
00:21:24,217 --> 00:21:25,518
Push!

397
00:21:25,585 --> 00:21:27,387
It says "push" there.

398
00:21:27,787 --> 00:21:29,489
You're right.

399
00:21:30,556 --> 00:21:31,591
Thank you.

400
00:21:44,404 --> 00:21:45,638
See you.

401
00:22:08,061 --> 00:22:09,228
Thank you.

402
00:22:09,962 --> 00:22:11,564
What is that scent?

403
00:22:14,934 --> 00:22:16,235
It's Eternal Egoist.

404
00:22:17,904 --> 00:22:18,938
Excuse me.

405
00:22:23,409 --> 00:22:25,445
Oh man! This is it!

406
00:22:25,511 --> 00:22:27,413
This is my home!

407
00:22:28,314 --> 00:22:30,249
But this bar…

408
00:22:30,316 --> 00:22:31,751
It got bigger.

409
00:22:31,818 --> 00:22:33,686
The business is good. Happy!

410
00:22:34,187 --> 00:22:36,389
Ta-da! Welcome!

411
00:22:36,456 --> 00:22:39,992
Shirasu! Wait, is it Mrs. Takuma now?

412
00:22:40,059 --> 00:22:42,662
No, Manager!

413
00:22:43,362 --> 00:22:46,466
-Didn't you hear? I got divorced!
-What?

414
00:22:46,532 --> 00:22:51,771
And now I'm working part-time
to make a living.

415
00:22:51,838 --> 00:22:53,339
Isn't it sad?

416
00:22:53,406 --> 00:22:57,143
Oh, if you are struggling,
do you want to work at our company?

417
00:22:57,210 --> 00:23:00,279
Manager! You are so kind,

418
00:23:00,346 --> 00:23:04,217
but I can't work under Sanchi.

419
00:23:04,283 --> 00:23:07,653
That tyrannical beast,
that anachronistic robot!

420
00:23:07,720 --> 00:23:11,324
Shirasu, Chief Sangenya is Manager's wife.

421
00:23:11,390 --> 00:23:15,194
Oh, that's right. Why did you marry
such a terrifying person?

422
00:23:15,261 --> 00:23:16,429
Well, forget that.

423
00:23:16,496 --> 00:23:18,498
More importantly,
please don't hire Shirasu.

424
00:23:18,564 --> 00:23:19,966
She just started to work here.

425
00:23:20,399 --> 00:23:23,603
If Teiko Real Estate wants to take her,
please go right ahead!

426
00:23:23,669 --> 00:23:24,904
Owner! That's not nice.

427
00:23:24,971 --> 00:23:27,406
Oh, but Kokoro, it's been a while.

428
00:23:27,473 --> 00:23:30,042
Kokoro wanted to see you too, Yashiro.

429
00:23:30,777 --> 00:23:35,915
Chichin pui-pui Puin! Puin!

430
00:23:35,982 --> 00:23:38,217
Oh, that sounds so nice!

431
00:23:38,284 --> 00:23:40,186
-Manager. I'm happy for you.
-Yes.

432
00:23:44,056 --> 00:23:48,427
Being with my client today made me wonder
what marriage is all about.

433
00:23:49,295 --> 00:23:51,230
That's what I want to know!

434
00:23:51,998 --> 00:23:53,366
Really?

435
00:23:53,432 --> 00:23:55,935
What do you call each other at home?

436
00:23:56,536 --> 00:23:59,205
She calls me "Manager"
and I call her "Sangenya".

437
00:23:59,806 --> 00:24:00,940
What?

438
00:24:01,007 --> 00:24:04,076
"Manager, here's breakfast!" Like that?

439
00:24:04,143 --> 00:24:05,812
It's like having an affair!

440
00:24:05,878 --> 00:24:07,814
Like, "Sangenya,
let's take a bath together?"

441
00:24:08,447 --> 00:24:09,749
I can't help but imagine it.

442
00:24:10,349 --> 00:24:14,520
But calling each other "Manager"
and "Sangenya" is kind of cool.

443
00:24:14,587 --> 00:24:16,389
It'll always feel like
a budding relationship.

444
00:24:18,658 --> 00:24:21,093
Hey, Niwano.
You're having some dirty thoughts!

445
00:24:21,160 --> 00:24:22,762
No, I was not.

446
00:24:22,829 --> 00:24:24,163
I was not at all!

447
00:24:24,230 --> 00:24:26,899
You dirty realtor! You dirty realtor!

448
00:24:26,966 --> 00:24:28,768
-You're dirty!
-What is it?

449
00:24:41,547 --> 00:24:42,982
This bedroom utilizes

450
00:24:43,049 --> 00:24:46,319
the current trend of couples
having separate bedrooms.

451
00:24:47,086 --> 00:24:48,888
There're two doors and when this wall

452
00:24:49,288 --> 00:24:52,725
is closed off, it becomes two rooms
and becomes one when this is opened.

453
00:24:53,693 --> 00:24:56,395
Hey, are you an idiot?

454
00:24:56,662 --> 00:24:59,198
Weren't you listening to me yesterday?

455
00:24:59,465 --> 00:25:00,700
I was listening.

456
00:25:00,967 --> 00:25:05,805
I want to divorce that snoring pig
and live by myself.

457
00:25:05,872 --> 00:25:09,008
That's why I told you to look
for a place even if it's a rental.

458
00:25:09,542 --> 00:25:12,578
Unfortunately for you, Mrs. Eriko Hanada,
your financial situation

459
00:25:12,645 --> 00:25:15,748
makes it impossible to rent a place,

460
00:25:15,815 --> 00:25:18,284
and it'll be impossible
for you to live alone.

461
00:25:18,751 --> 00:25:20,653
What? How rude.

462
00:25:20,720 --> 00:25:25,358
If we sell that house
and I get half of the assets, I'll manage.

463
00:25:25,424 --> 00:25:28,794
Unfortunately, that house is
¥25 million at most with the land.

464
00:25:29,295 --> 00:25:30,863
After paying taxes and halving it,

465
00:25:30,930 --> 00:25:35,134
the remaining funds will not support you
for the next 30 to 40 years of your life.

466
00:25:36,402 --> 00:25:38,905
Then I'll work at a convenience store.

467
00:25:38,971 --> 00:25:41,641
They currently have a shortage of workers.

468
00:25:41,707 --> 00:25:44,110
Working at a convenience store
is not just working the register.

469
00:25:44,176 --> 00:25:45,478
Processing various payments,

470
00:25:45,544 --> 00:25:48,281
arranging delivery services,
arranging dry cleaning,

471
00:25:48,347 --> 00:25:51,717
stocking and re-arranging shelves.
It's a very tough job that requires

472
00:25:51,784 --> 00:25:52,952
agility and strength,

473
00:25:53,019 --> 00:25:54,587
a fast thinking brain

474
00:25:54,654 --> 00:25:56,455
and a broad range of knowledge.

475
00:25:59,659 --> 00:26:02,695
-Is that true?
-Yes, it is.

476
00:26:02,762 --> 00:26:06,132
In addition, that cashmere sweater
you are wearing

477
00:26:06,599 --> 00:26:10,770
is probably more than the pay
for working seven hours for seven days.

478
00:26:12,405 --> 00:26:14,907
-What? Is that true?
-Yes, it is.

479
00:26:15,708 --> 00:26:19,745
Thinking that you are able to work
because the government is promoting

480
00:26:19,812 --> 00:26:22,048
"dynamic engagement
of all citizens", is a mistake.

481
00:26:22,114 --> 00:26:24,350
It's too late for you
to get back into the workforce,

482
00:26:24,417 --> 00:26:28,020
and working to be independent
is not the only value in a person's life.

483
00:26:28,921 --> 00:26:30,957
-Is that true?
-Y… Yes, it is.

484
00:26:31,023 --> 00:26:33,626
-What am I going to do?
-What should she do?

485
00:26:34,226 --> 00:26:36,996
It is to put all your life

486
00:26:37,063 --> 00:26:40,967
into the one job only you,
Mrs. Eriko, can do.

487
00:26:41,367 --> 00:26:43,436
But you said I can't get back
into the workforce.

488
00:26:43,502 --> 00:26:46,439
The other day, when we visited
your home for the first time,

489
00:26:46,505 --> 00:26:48,541
you had something
wrapped around your slippers.

490
00:26:48,607 --> 00:26:49,775
When I looked at it closely,

491
00:26:49,842 --> 00:26:51,777
it was a dusting cloth.

492
00:26:52,545 --> 00:26:54,547
It's a practical cleaning method

493
00:26:54,613 --> 00:26:56,248
to clean and walk at the same time.

494
00:26:57,149 --> 00:27:00,252
Inside the fridge was an ice cold pen.

495
00:27:00,319 --> 00:27:02,788
When I looked closely,

496
00:27:02,855 --> 00:27:06,125
the eggs had an expiration date on it.

497
00:27:06,192 --> 00:27:08,861
If it's a hassle to put away,
leave it where you always use it.

498
00:27:08,928 --> 00:27:13,132
It's a very practical storage method
even if it's in a fridge.

499
00:27:13,499 --> 00:27:17,069
A primitive idea to take in
the laundry from the balcony.

500
00:27:17,370 --> 00:27:20,072
Those unique tricks in life
created from laziness,

501
00:27:20,506 --> 00:27:23,175
have no use whatsoever in society.

502
00:27:23,242 --> 00:27:26,379
But it's a very valuable,
and wonderful method.

503
00:27:26,879 --> 00:27:29,815
Huge servings of homemade food
that's easy to make,

504
00:27:29,882 --> 00:27:33,419
the wrinkled handkerchiefs,
and the unpaired socks.

505
00:27:33,486 --> 00:27:36,389
This unpretentious,
untidy and laid-back lifestyle

506
00:27:36,655 --> 00:27:38,290
is what comforts Mr. Haruo.

507
00:27:38,357 --> 00:27:42,294
It created a home for him
where he was able to restore his energy.

508
00:27:43,629 --> 00:27:45,531
I think that's a bit too much.

509
00:27:46,399 --> 00:27:48,567
You are the professional housewife

510
00:27:48,634 --> 00:27:52,071
of the Hanada family,
who knows how to cut corners!

511
00:27:53,506 --> 00:27:56,575
That is your calling, Mrs. Eriko.

512
00:27:58,144 --> 00:28:02,882
-Is that true?
-Yes, it is.

513
00:28:02,948 --> 00:28:07,520
In addition, what I just said
is not my opinion.

514
00:28:07,820 --> 00:28:09,055
What?

515
00:28:09,121 --> 00:28:11,924
It was something your husband said.

516
00:28:12,358 --> 00:28:15,027
-That's a lie.
-It is not a lie!

517
00:28:17,563 --> 00:28:21,367
Then that means you met
with my husband without me?

518
00:28:21,434 --> 00:28:22,568
Yes.

519
00:28:22,635 --> 00:28:25,905
He told me about the date
you and Mr. Haruo went on,

520
00:28:25,971 --> 00:28:28,908
at an aquarium when you two just met.

521
00:28:29,508 --> 00:28:33,079
An Aquarium? Did I go?

522
00:28:36,449 --> 00:28:40,086
You saw a dolphin show there, right?

523
00:28:43,889 --> 00:28:45,024
I did!

524
00:28:46,459 --> 00:28:50,362
When he saw you watching the dolphin show

525
00:28:50,429 --> 00:28:52,498
with your mouth open,

526
00:28:53,065 --> 00:28:57,970
he decided that he wanted to live
the rest of his life

527
00:28:58,037 --> 00:29:00,372
with this laid-back girl.

528
00:29:01,974 --> 00:29:04,810
You were seated in the first row
and got really wet, right?

529
00:29:05,911 --> 00:29:06,979
Yes, we did!

530
00:29:07,046 --> 00:29:09,682
Ever since the day you two
saw the dolphin show together,

531
00:29:09,748 --> 00:29:15,254
Mr. Haruo has continued to cherish
all the charming sides of you.

532
00:29:18,724 --> 00:29:22,595
But even so, to live
with that pig-like snore until I die

533
00:29:22,661 --> 00:29:24,997
and to be in the same grave as him?

534
00:29:25,064 --> 00:29:28,134
For that matter, please come this way.

535
00:29:32,171 --> 00:29:35,341
If you purchase this property,

536
00:29:35,608 --> 00:29:39,111
that grave will come for free.

537
00:29:39,645 --> 00:29:41,113
It comes with a grave?

538
00:29:41,714 --> 00:29:43,983
It's a grave specifically
for you, Mrs. Eriko.

539
00:29:44,316 --> 00:29:45,584
Specifically for me?

540
00:29:46,452 --> 00:29:49,088
If you consider the relationship
with Mr. Haruo as something

541
00:29:49,155 --> 00:29:50,756
limited to this lifetime,
then it's precious.

542
00:29:51,357 --> 00:29:53,526
The fact that you will have
a separate grave

543
00:29:53,592 --> 00:29:57,730
will make your marriage vows
in this lifetime something special.

544
00:29:59,098 --> 00:30:01,066
I truly believe so.

545
00:30:15,848 --> 00:30:17,716
Just this lifetime?

546
00:30:20,119 --> 00:30:21,654
Oh, it's Mr. Haruo.

547
00:30:23,055 --> 00:30:26,225
Mr. Haruo has already previewed this home.

548
00:30:26,525 --> 00:30:28,594
-What?
-Please, come in.

549
00:30:29,628 --> 00:30:31,630
Eriko, what do you think of this home?

550
00:30:47,246 --> 00:30:48,581
I think it might work.

551
00:30:49,415 --> 00:30:51,951
Mr. Haruo Hanada and Mrs. Eriko Hanada,

552
00:30:52,017 --> 00:30:56,088
will you purchase this home
for ¥46 million?

553
00:30:57,556 --> 00:30:58,791
We will.

554
00:31:02,228 --> 00:31:03,495
I've got them.

555
00:31:04,330 --> 00:31:07,600
Then please sign this application form.

556
00:31:14,673 --> 00:31:19,011
Thank you for finding a house
with separate bedrooms.

557
00:31:20,079 --> 00:31:24,316
I will now be freed
from Eriko's dreadful teeth grinding.

558
00:31:25,818 --> 00:31:27,653
-Hurry up!
-Coming!

559
00:31:33,392 --> 00:31:36,262
How did you find out about the aquarium?

560
00:31:36,729 --> 00:31:39,131
You sure are good, Chief Sangenya.

561
00:31:39,198 --> 00:31:40,699
That story is made up.

562
00:31:41,934 --> 00:31:43,769
Couples in the olden days
usually went on a date

563
00:31:43,836 --> 00:31:45,504
at an amusement park or the aquarium.

564
00:31:45,971 --> 00:31:47,239
Is that true?

565
00:31:47,306 --> 00:31:49,408
When they go to an aquarium,
they'll see a dolphin show.

566
00:31:49,475 --> 00:31:51,310
They usually get wet.

567
00:31:51,610 --> 00:31:53,279
But the fact they had the front row seats…

568
00:31:53,345 --> 00:31:55,914
They don't remember such details!

569
00:31:55,981 --> 00:31:58,384
So if I insist that they were seated
in front, they will agree.

570
00:31:58,851 --> 00:32:00,185
That was all a lie?

571
00:32:01,120 --> 00:32:03,322
It's to sell a house!

572
00:32:04,723 --> 00:32:06,458
-Yes.
-It's green.

573
00:32:07,760 --> 00:32:08,827
Ah, yes!

574
00:32:14,833 --> 00:32:18,103
This lobby has infrared sensors all over,

575
00:32:18,170 --> 00:32:19,738
preventing suspicious persons
from entering.

576
00:32:20,072 --> 00:32:23,509
Also, there's a 24-hour concierge service,

577
00:32:23,575 --> 00:32:26,378
so it's a very popular property
for celebrities as well.

578
00:32:29,014 --> 00:32:30,282
Please come this way.

579
00:32:36,922 --> 00:32:41,827
This elevator requires a physical key
and your fingerprint to function.

580
00:32:46,198 --> 00:32:47,866
This is it.

581
00:32:47,933 --> 00:32:49,802
The retina of the eye is used as

582
00:32:49,868 --> 00:32:51,603
the biometric authentication
to unlock the doors.

583
00:32:53,272 --> 00:32:54,807
It's a bother when you are in a rush.

584
00:32:55,774 --> 00:32:59,545
However, the likelihood of people
having the same retina is low,

585
00:32:59,611 --> 00:33:02,815
so it's a perfect security measure.

586
00:33:03,415 --> 00:33:04,483
Please come in.

587
00:33:07,586 --> 00:33:09,288
-And this is--
-What?

588
00:33:10,789 --> 00:33:11,857
What's the matter?

589
00:33:13,559 --> 00:33:17,663
"I found Nikumaru previewing our condo.

590
00:33:17,730 --> 00:33:20,799
It'll be such a nuisance
if he becomes my next door neighbor.

591
00:33:20,866 --> 00:33:22,968
Laugh, laugh, laugh."

592
00:33:23,469 --> 00:33:27,406
Which part of this condo's
security system is excellent?

593
00:33:30,242 --> 00:33:35,948
Why do I have to deal with such slander
just for looking at a house?

594
00:33:39,885 --> 00:33:42,254
-Adachi, was it?
-Yes.

595
00:33:43,288 --> 00:33:46,658
You don't get it at all.

596
00:33:48,460 --> 00:33:52,064
Change!

597
00:33:54,633 --> 00:33:55,968
I'm going to the restroom.

598
00:33:57,536 --> 00:33:58,537
I'm going to the restroom.

599
00:34:00,305 --> 00:34:01,807
Welcome back.

600
00:34:02,174 --> 00:34:03,375
Manager.

601
00:34:04,276 --> 00:34:07,613
The property in Mitaka with a partition
was sold to the Hanadas.

602
00:34:08,213 --> 00:34:11,049
It wasn't Niwano, but I sold it.

603
00:34:11,350 --> 00:34:12,851
Yeah! Sangenya!

604
00:34:14,119 --> 00:34:15,320
Good work!

605
00:34:16,488 --> 00:34:18,590
How about you, Adachi?
How did it go with Mr. Nikumaru?

606
00:34:21,026 --> 00:34:23,629
I showed him to the property
with the latest security,

607
00:34:23,695 --> 00:34:24,696
but he didn't like it.

608
00:34:25,564 --> 00:34:27,299
He said he wants a different realtor.

609
00:34:28,167 --> 00:34:29,168
I see.

610
00:34:29,835 --> 00:34:32,971
I will take care of Mr. Nikumaru.

611
00:34:33,505 --> 00:34:36,442
I will sell him a house for sure!

612
00:34:48,887 --> 00:34:50,289
Darn it!

613
00:34:50,956 --> 00:34:53,525
-Darn it! Darn it!
-A festival? A darned festival?

614
00:34:54,393 --> 00:34:55,561
En garde.

615
00:34:56,195 --> 00:34:57,396
Prêt, allez.

616
00:35:02,267 --> 00:35:03,435
Adachi is the winner!

617
00:35:11,910 --> 00:35:15,314
I feel a certain intensity
from you today, Mr. Adachi.

618
00:35:16,014 --> 00:35:18,851
-What?
-I admit total defeat. Excuse me.

619
00:35:21,753 --> 00:35:22,888
Mr. Rusudo.

620
00:35:25,657 --> 00:35:29,962
I was thinking of asking you something
if I won against you today.

621
00:35:30,796 --> 00:35:34,333
What do you do for work, Rusudo?

622
00:35:36,401 --> 00:35:38,937
I'd like to know,
if you don't mind telling me.

623
00:35:41,139 --> 00:35:43,408
It's nothing that special…

624
00:35:45,944 --> 00:35:47,513
but I'm in real estate.

625
00:35:49,581 --> 00:35:51,383
I'm in real estate too!

626
00:35:54,620 --> 00:35:56,688
-The same thing.
-Yes sir.

627
00:35:56,755 --> 00:36:02,461
So that person named Machi Sangenya
is a thorn in your side?

628
00:36:03,161 --> 00:36:04,162
Yes, she's a thorn.

629
00:36:05,697 --> 00:36:06,932
-A thorn?
-Huh?

630
00:36:07,799 --> 00:36:10,335
It's kind of an old-fashioned term,
a thorn.

631
00:36:10,402 --> 00:36:13,705
Is it? Everyone is not using it?

632
00:36:14,373 --> 00:36:17,643
It must be special
when you say it, Mr. Rusudo.

633
00:36:20,879 --> 00:36:22,014
What am I saying?

634
00:36:22,681 --> 00:36:26,151
So I want to do better than Sanchi,

635
00:36:26,218 --> 00:36:28,053
but I haven't been able to.

636
00:36:29,621 --> 00:36:31,890
Do you hate that person?

637
00:36:32,224 --> 00:36:34,726
I don't hate her. I respect her too.

638
00:36:35,360 --> 00:36:37,896
I just want to win. I want to win.

639
00:36:38,297 --> 00:36:39,498
I want to win at all costs!

640
00:36:41,433 --> 00:36:42,734
I see.

641
00:36:44,202 --> 00:36:47,573
That expression on your face
when you say you want to win…

642
00:36:48,807 --> 00:36:50,042
is very charming.

643
00:37:01,353 --> 00:37:03,989
It's a different drink. Why?

644
00:37:04,056 --> 00:37:05,958
That's because it belongs
to the person next to you.

645
00:37:06,024 --> 00:37:07,159
What?

646
00:37:10,162 --> 00:37:11,296
I apologize.

647
00:37:13,298 --> 00:37:16,168
-Please give him the same drink.
-As you wish.

648
00:37:17,703 --> 00:37:20,005
So were we talking about a thorn?

649
00:37:20,072 --> 00:37:23,408
What? Oh, yes, the thorn.

650
00:37:24,109 --> 00:37:26,411
A thorn in my side.

651
00:37:29,247 --> 00:37:30,349
A thorn?

652
00:37:31,016 --> 00:37:33,585
Your wife is coming home late again?

653
00:37:34,786 --> 00:37:36,388
I feel sorry for you Yashiro.

654
00:37:37,022 --> 00:37:39,691
It's different from our time
at Sanchi Real Estate by the sea.

655
00:37:39,758 --> 00:37:44,196
I feel like Sangenya's eyes
have changed since we returned to Tokyo.

656
00:37:44,997 --> 00:37:48,533
I can't tell her not to work
since she's so talented.

657
00:37:49,301 --> 00:37:51,536
She's definitely
a lot more capable than me.

658
00:37:51,603 --> 00:37:56,408
Well, I am disappointed
but that's the part…

659
00:37:56,475 --> 00:37:59,111
You love her for it!

660
00:37:59,177 --> 00:38:00,479
I don't know.

661
00:38:01,013 --> 00:38:03,415
Creepy!

662
00:38:03,482 --> 00:38:06,718
Mika! You went through a divorce,
and you still don't get it?

663
00:38:06,785 --> 00:38:09,688
Love is complicated.
Sometimes you don't know

664
00:38:09,755 --> 00:38:11,490
if you love them or hate them.

665
00:38:12,157 --> 00:38:14,326
-Is that true?
-Is that so?

666
00:38:14,393 --> 00:38:16,995
Yes, it is! Love is a distorted substance.

667
00:38:17,529 --> 00:38:22,968
That's right, Mr. and Mrs. Hanada,
whom Chief Sangenya sold a house to,

668
00:38:23,669 --> 00:38:26,405
weren't certain
whether they loved each other or not.

669
00:38:27,272 --> 00:38:30,676
Why did I get rid of Takuma?

670
00:38:35,047 --> 00:38:36,815
-Water!
-What?

671
00:38:36,882 --> 00:38:38,383
Water? Get it yourself!

672
00:39:05,110 --> 00:39:06,445
Chief Sangenya.

673
00:39:10,449 --> 00:39:11,750
This is Mr. Nikumaru.

674
00:39:12,751 --> 00:39:14,119
We've been waiting for you.

675
00:39:15,454 --> 00:39:17,589
This time, it better be a safe place.

676
00:39:18,990 --> 00:39:20,225
It's a sure thing.

677
00:39:20,826 --> 00:39:24,663
My boss,
Machi Sangenya, is a legendary realtor.

678
00:39:25,197 --> 00:39:28,467
She'll find a property
to your liking for sure.

679
00:39:31,369 --> 00:39:33,572
So? Where is that property?

680
00:39:35,707 --> 00:39:39,144
I will sell you this house
for ¥100 million.

681
00:39:39,811 --> 00:39:40,912
Which one?

682
00:39:43,749 --> 00:39:45,117
This house.

683
00:39:46,485 --> 00:39:47,719
It's a ramshackle house.

684
00:39:48,854 --> 00:39:51,757
This is a perfect house for you.

685
00:39:51,823 --> 00:39:55,060
Why? Why? Why?

686
00:39:55,127 --> 00:39:56,495
Wow, isn't that Nikumaru?

687
00:39:57,796 --> 00:40:01,767
Hey, treat us to something.
You make a bundle, right?

688
00:40:01,833 --> 00:40:03,034
Hey! Don't ignore us!

689
00:40:03,101 --> 00:40:06,805
You used to be funny,
but you're burnt out these days!

690
00:40:07,839 --> 00:40:12,010
-Burnt out! Burnt out!
-Hey!

691
00:40:13,078 --> 00:40:14,513
Who are you?

692
00:40:14,579 --> 00:40:17,282
Let's discuss things at the station.

693
00:40:17,349 --> 00:40:18,383
What?

694
00:40:21,386 --> 00:40:22,788
Oh no! Let's go!

695
00:40:25,090 --> 00:40:27,392
That was so cool!

696
00:40:27,459 --> 00:40:28,760
Thank you very much.

697
00:40:28,827 --> 00:40:30,929
It's my first time seeing a real cop.

698
00:40:34,666 --> 00:40:36,067
Who are you?

699
00:40:36,134 --> 00:40:38,637
Pardon me. Here is my card.

700
00:40:39,905 --> 00:40:40,906
KENJI RUSUDO

701
00:40:43,408 --> 00:40:44,576
You are a realtor?

702
00:40:44,643 --> 00:40:47,979
Yes, I'm a freelance realtor.

703
00:40:48,480 --> 00:40:49,981
You are Mr. Nikumaru, right?

704
00:40:50,715 --> 00:40:51,716
Yes.

705
00:40:52,083 --> 00:40:54,953
I always enjoy watching your videos.

706
00:40:55,987 --> 00:40:58,390
-Really?
-I'm a subscriber as well.

707
00:40:59,758 --> 00:41:01,760
Perfect timing!

708
00:41:01,827 --> 00:41:05,230
You're quick witted, so could you
look for a house for me?

709
00:41:05,964 --> 00:41:09,267
I'm annoyed they brought me
to this shack here!

710
00:41:09,334 --> 00:41:10,735
You guys are fired!

711
00:41:10,802 --> 00:41:14,306
I'm changing to this man here!

712
00:41:16,541 --> 00:41:17,676
Is it okay?

713
00:41:18,910 --> 00:41:20,145
Is it okay?

714
00:41:20,679 --> 00:41:23,882
It's fine. We'll come along as well.

715
00:41:35,460 --> 00:41:38,330
How do you like it, Mr. Nikumaru?

716
00:41:52,244 --> 00:41:53,945
What do you think this means?

717
00:42:01,620 --> 00:42:05,957
This is the video I made
when I first became a YouTuber.

718
00:42:11,129 --> 00:42:12,797
Nikumaru TV.

719
00:42:14,933 --> 00:42:19,638
Today, I found this thing!
It's a home-taped video!

720
00:42:20,005 --> 00:42:22,607
My father and mother got divorced

721
00:42:22,674 --> 00:42:25,810
and so I was raised
at my grandmother's home.

722
00:42:25,877 --> 00:42:28,280
This is the video from back then.

723
00:42:29,848 --> 00:42:31,149
Tonight, we'll watch the moon.

724
00:42:31,216 --> 00:42:32,217
CHILDHOOD NIKUMARU

725
00:42:32,817 --> 00:42:36,254
Grandma, will you eat
the dumplings I made?

726
00:42:37,522 --> 00:42:41,159
Is this it? I shall eat it now.

727
00:42:43,695 --> 00:42:45,463
This is not a dumpling.

728
00:42:46,164 --> 00:42:47,465
Oh my!

729
00:42:48,667 --> 00:42:50,902
This is a ping pong ball!

730
00:42:50,969 --> 00:42:52,837
My prank was a success!

731
00:42:56,107 --> 00:42:59,010
This house is like my grandmother's home.
